        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Jewish Foster Home and Orphan Asylum&#44;<lb/>
                Mill Street&#44; near Chew.<lb/></p>
            <p>S.M. Fleischman&#44;
                Superintendent.<lb/></p>			<p>Germantown&#44; Phila.&#44; March 26&#44; 1886<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir and friend&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>It affords me much pleasure in writ&#45;<lb/>ing you this letter&#91;.&#93; I am an inmate of<lb/> the Jewish Foster Home and Orphan<lb/> Asylum. I congratulate you for being<lb/> a &#34;teacher of Judaism&#34; thirty five years.<lb/> I hope that the &#34;Lord&#34; will give you<lb/> strength and vigor enough to continue<lb/> doing as much good as you have done.<lb/> We thank you for the nice present you<lb/> sent us on &#34;Purim&#34;. I hope that all<lb/> the &#34;sons of Israel&#34; will follow in your<lb/> noble and pious ways&#44; <sic>especialy</sic> the<lb/> children of our home.<lb/></p>
            <p>Respectfully&#44; Herbert A. Solomon<lb/></p>
            <p>In the name of all the children.<lb/> <hi rend="underline">over</hi><lb/></p>
            
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Dear Doctor.<lb/></p>
            <p>Although a stranger to you<lb/> please permit me to add my best wishes.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours<lb/>
                S.M. Fleischman<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
